## 13. What Does NOT Diminish the Run

A << f("raw.wins") >>-<< f("raw.losses") >> record raises familiar objections: the conference was weak, the bracket was soft, the opponents were hurt, the scoreboard was padded.
Each was tested; the data does not support any of them.

| Objection | Verdict | Where |
|---|---|---|
| The East was historically weak | No. The West–East rating gap was << f("gap.west_east") >> pts/game (<< f("gap.pct", "{:.0f}") >>th percentile of West dominance); the West led by more in << f("gap.pct_more_dominant") >> of seasons since 1984. | §3 |
| The bracket was soft | No. Games-weighted opponent rating was << f("opp.srs_weighted") >> (<< f("opp.srs_pct", "{:.0f}") >>th percentile), the median champion's schedule. | §3–§4 |
| The early-round teams were fading | A little, at the edges. The 76ers and Cavaliers rated ~1.2–1.5 pts below their season form, but on a handful of games each; the Spurs went the other way and rose +6.2. Adjusting the run for opponents' actual playoff form still leaves it at << f("adj_po.margin", "{:+.1f}") >>, narrowly best on record. | §5 |
| The margins are garbage-time padding | No. On a wins-only rating that never sees a point margin, the Knicks still rank first of << f("raw.n_champions") >>. | §11 |
| The high-scoring era inflated the margin | Mostly no. The scoring is better shooting, not a faster game; per possession both the raw and adjusted margins stay first. Only the harsher scoring-share adjustment drops the raw margin to 3rd. | §14 |
| An opponent was injured | No. Opponents were << f("health.avg") >>% healthy on average; the Spurs and Hawks were at << f("health.spurs") >>%. | §9 |

The one thing that genuinely tempers the claim is not on this list.
It is the shortness of a 19-game run: when every champion is allowed the same uncertainty, the Knicks are the single best only about << f("hier.p_rank1", "{:.0f}") >>% of the time (§10–§11).

Each objection is treated in full, with why it seemed plausible and exactly what the data showed, in the companion document *The Investigation* (Appendix A).

